{
    "metadata": {
      "version": "2026-04",
      "description": "Comprehensive mapper from Interactive Brokers (IB) futures root symbols to Bloomberg active contract tickers",
      "bloomberg_convention": {
        "most_active_ticker": "Root symbol + 'A' suffix → always points to the highest open-interest contract, e.g. ESA Index",
        "yellow_keys": {
          "Index": "Equity and volatility index futures",
          "Comdty": "Commodities, energy, metals, ags, and fixed income futures",
          "Curncy": "FX futures"
        },
        "notes": [
          "Micro contracts (MES, MNQ, MGC, MCL, etc.) map to the SAME Bloomberg active ticker as their full-size parent because they reference the same underlying.",
          "Bloomberg 'A' suffix is the most-active (highest open interest) rolling ticker. The 'generic N-th month' variant uses a number suffix (e.g. TY1 Comdty = 1st generic 10-Year T-Note).",
          "ICE and Eurex instruments follow the same 'XA <Key>' convention as CME.",
          "Sources: CME Group Bloomberg cheat sheets (official), University of Calgary Bloomberg guide, Bloomberg BLPAPI Core User Guide, CME FX Bloomberg User Guide."
        ]
      }
    },
  
